Because I always forget...

"For finding a file name below the current directory
find . -name "filename.txt"

"Find a directory below the current directory
find . -typ d -name folderName

Use -iname for ignored case


Export sql as file - I had to write somewhere that sql was allowed to write
Select user_email from wp_users LIMIT 10 INTO OUTFILE '/tmp/emails.csv' FIELDS TERMINATED BY ',' ENCLOSED BY '"' LINES TERMINATED BY '\n';

